node.text:
Connect with me beyond the scroll! Sign up for my newsletter for photography tips (link in bio!)✨

When I opened up my Ask Me Anything, I was struck by how many of you are navigating the challenge of finding balance with social media. But honestly… is it that surprising? It’s something I’ve wrestled with for the past six years, and seeing so many of you feel the same way just reaffirms what I’ve been reflecting on lately.

Over the past few weeks, I’ve been in and out of socials, trying to find a way forward—one that still inspires me to engage, share my passion, and grow this photography community, but without the constant noise. More and more, I’ve been craving depth—real connection beyond the scroll.

That’s why I’m pouring more energy into my newsletter—a space to share photography tips and behind-the-scenes moments without the algorithm deciding who sees them. I don’t want to limit providing value to just mentorship calls—I want my newsletter to be a space where like-minded people can grow, get inspired, and share their love for photography and nature. 🌊

In the coming weeks, I’ll be sharing anything from camera settings, a deep dive into underwater photography to my favorite Lightroom settings! If that sounds like something you’d love, join me through the link in my bio—can’t wait to share more with you!

So, consider this both an invitation and a bit of accountability for myself 😉 

Hopefully, it’ll help you on your own photography & social media journey too!

Hope to see you there! 💙

PS. In my quest for a healthier balance with socials, I also just ordered a Brick—a device that temporarily removes distractions from my phone. I’ll keep you posted on how it goes! 😊🤞

#photographytips #sonyambassador #liveyourpassion #miastawinski #womeninphotography #womenphotographers #mentorship #photographymentorship #underwaterphotography #wildlifephotography #wildlifeconservation #lightroom #sonya7iii 
 #leopards #gorillaconservation #lionphotography
Love the flies on the lion 😍😍😍
@paigedeas so happy to hear that, thanks!! Seems like such a common feeling these days!! I am gonna test out @getbrick - will let you know if it works for me!
LOVED seeing your newsletter pop up - I've definitely been feeling the same way about social media!
These are all beautiful shots 😍 Signed up!

I would love too! And yesss, i feel you, i have for years and years offline days, until 11 am i am online, i do this between 4-7 days a week and i love them! Real life is so much better than the noise and fakeness of social media. I do check my email at my laptop, but that’s it.
Who’s the lucky person who gets to take photos of you on the prowl for beautiful animals? Thank them for us…even if it’s your man Frotto.
